and everyone else's parents let them go out. I'm so fortunate to be the overly protected only girl out of five boys. I think a summer to-do list is the only thing there is to do right now.

Everythings slowly falling back into place. But instead of just cruising along with it, I feel scared. In a really strange way that also makes me excited. :) This is far from finished, I've only worked on it for about half an hour so far. I'm debating between nude or clothed I'm thinking about getting my weave cut short again. I'm moving to Edmonds in three months.
Well that was a bad idea Livvy

I honestly didn't think that this would happen to us ever again. 
I can't say that you let me down, because I stopped trusting you after the fifth relapse. Things were doing so well, you were doing so well. There's no excuse for you to rewind all of that progress. You don't have a disease, this isn't all about you, no one out there is deliberatley trying to hurt you. Take care of your family, take care of you. I've been forgiving as much as humanly possible. I want to step up and be the parent? I'd probably do a much better job than yourself.

If there's one thing you've taught me, it's that people don't change.

everyone's a princess "i was destined to fly the hang glider" haha i love my brother for anyone who knows how to interpret dreams, i dreamt last night that all of my teeth fell out. then i had to get veneers and keep it secret, but nonetheless i was just as happy.

i decided to make use of it and pull out my dusty acryllic set. oil is better, i know. it took about an hour to sketch this thing out and paint it, and it turned out looking a lot darker and more gothic than i intended haha, maybe its the demonic hormones just roaring to get outside of me. sloppy thirds four bowls of cran-vanilla crunch cereal, and im still going @;@
mums'n i birthday twins big spender

i know i know, everyone's dying to feast their eyes upon my vacation pictures. so far, it's been a pretty life changing experience, but im ready for it to end. i miss being pale >:0 hahaha, my grandpa tripped over the ticket line at disneyland, hitting his head on the pavement afterwards. they sent dopey dwarf in with a band aid to personally escort him to disney's medical center. juss' chillin wit clyde and seamore dolphins feel like hot dogs! corkie! or should i say one of the many "shamus", but still mildly cute?

has been home to many firsts:
first wild vulture sighting
first time watching an autistic man with "silent turrets"
first time meeting pluto the dog
first time missing my twin in the past five months
first ride in a 12 seater dune buggie
first time smelling a sea lion
first time being in a controlled elevator that dropped 10 stories
first time giving a nacho platter to a homeless man
and for my personal favorite, first time seeing THE VANS WARPED TOUR audience in san francisco, hahah tight black pants and messy hair everywhere, it was so horrible


i would have pictures, but i dont know how to put them up. brittany, you teach me when i get back. anyway, it's not a lot to brag about. i miss everyone more than i ever have, and just knowing that i have to go back to renton afterwards makes me want to lock monique in a cage for an extra week. i havent been able to use the phone and/or computer for a while.

next stop: sea world!
hahaha, my parents reserved a "dinner with shamu"
